<subSubSection id="C308EFA48109D104072A5F4EF8DBFA6D" pageId="10" pageNumber="192" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BADBC2F8109D104072A5F4EF8DBFA6D" blockId="10.[255,1088,1380,1428]" pageId="10" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="B966603D8109D104072A5F4EFBAEFA80" bold="true" box="[282,409,1380,1401]" pageId="10" pageNumber="192">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for our friend Betty Juarez. The specific epithet is a noun in apposition to 
<taxonomicName id="4C12C7AC8109D104045C5F55F8D3FA6D" box="[620,740,1407,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Meibomeus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="192" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B966603D8109D104045C5F55F8D3FA6D" box="[620,740,1407,1428]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="192">Meibomeus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
